      "answerHtml": "<p>Let \\(X\\) be a real normed space. If \\(A, B \\subset X\\) are nonempty disjoint convex subsets of \\(X\\), such that \\(A\\) is compact and \\(B\\) is closed, then there exist a continuous linear functional \\(L \\in X^*\\) with \\(L \\neq 0\\) and real numbers \\(\\alpha < \\beta\\) such that:\n        <div class=\"formula\">\\[\n        L(a) \\le \\alpha < \\beta \\le L(b) \\qquad \\forall a \\in A, \\, \\forall b \\in B.\n        \\]</div>\n        This is the strict separation theorem, establishing a positive gap between the values of the functional on \\(A\\) and \\(B\\).</p>"
