      "keyStepsHtml": "<div class=\"formula\">\\[\n        H = \\{x \\in X : L(x) = \\alpha\\},\n        \\]</div><div class=\"formula\">\\[\n          L(a) \\le \\alpha \\le L(b) \\qquad \\forall a \\in A, \\, \\forall b \\in B.\n          \\]</div>",
      "answerHtml": "<p>Let \\(X\\) be a real normed space (or the real part of functionals if \\(X\\) is complex). A hyperplane \\(H\\) is a set of the form:\n        <div class=\"formula\">\\[\n        H = \\{x \\in X : L(x) = \\alpha\\},\n        \\]</div>\n        where \\(L \\in X^*\\) is a continuous linear functional with \\(L \\neq 0\\) and \\(\\alpha \\in \\mathbb{R}\\).\n        - \\(H\\) **separates** two subsets \\(A, B \\subset X\\) if:\n          <div class=\"formula\">\\[\n          L(a) \\le \\alpha \\le L(b) \\qquad \\forall a \\in A, \\, \\forall b \\in B.\n          \\]</div>\n        - \\(H\\) **strictly separates** \\(A\\) and \\(B\\) if there exists \\(\\varepsilon > 0\\) such that:\n          <div class=\"formula\">\\[\n          L(a) \\le \\alpha - \\varepsilon \\quad \\text{and} \\quad L(b) \\ge \\alpha + \\varepsilon \\qquad \\forall a \\in A, \\, \\forall b \\in B.\n          \\]</div></p>"
