      "keyStepsHtml": "<div class=\"formula\">\\[\n        \\|x\\|_X \\le \\liminf_{n\\to\\infty} \\|x_n\\|_X.\n        \\]</div><div class=\"formula\">\\[\n        \\|x\\|_X = \\sup \\{ |L(x)| : L \\in X^*, \\, \\|L\\|_{X^*} \\le 1 \\}.\n        \\]</div>",
      "answerHtml": "<p><strong>Proof sketch / Polya view:</strong> The conclusion is a norm inequality under weak convergence. Test the weak limit with unit dual functionals, pass to the limit in scalars, bound by the liminf of the norms, then take the supremum using Hahn-Banach. <em>Question focus:</em> State and prove lower semicontinuity with respect to weak convergence of \\(x\\mapsto\\|x\\|\\).</p><p>If \\(x_n \\rightharpoonup x\\) in a normed space \\(X\\), then:\n        <div class=\"formula\">\\[\n        \\|x\\|_X \\le \\liminf_{n\\to\\infty} \\|x_n\\|_X.\n        \\]</div>\n        <em>Proof:</em> By a corollary of the Hahn-Banach Theorem, the norm on \\(X\\) can be characterized as:\n        <div class=\"formula\">\\[\n        \\|x\\|_X = \\sup \\{ |L(x)| : L \\in X^*, \\, \\|L\\|_{X^*} \\le 1 \\}.\n        \\]</div>\n        Let \\(L \\in X^*\\) with \\(\\|L\\|_{X^*} \\le 1\\). Since \\(x_n \\rightharpoonup x\\), we have \\(L(x_n) \\to L(x)\\) in \\(\\mathbb{K}\\). Thus:\n        <div class=\"formula\">\\[\n        |L(x)| = \\lim_{n\\to\\infty} |L(x_n)| = \\liminf_{n\\to\\infty} |L(x_n)| \\le \\liminf_{n\\to\\infty} (\\|L\\|_{X^*} \\|x_n\\|_X) \\le \\liminf_{n\\to\\infty} \\|x_n\\|_X.\n        \\]</div>\n        Taking the supremum over all \\(L \\in X^*\\) with \\(\\|L\\|_{X^*} \\le 1\\) on the left-hand side yields:\n        <div class=\"formula\">\\[\n        \\|x\\|_X \\le \\liminf_{n\\to\\infty} \\|x_n\\|_X.\n        \\]</div></p>"
