      "answerHtml": "<p>Let \\(X\\) be a normed space and \\(X^*\\) its dual space. A sequence \\((L_n)\\) in \\(X^*\\) converges weak-star to \\(L \\in X^*\\) (denoted by \\(L_n \\overset{*}{\\rightharpoonup} L\\)) if:\n        <div class=\"formula\">\\[\n        \\lim_{n\\to\\infty} L_n(x) = L(x) \\qquad \\forall x \\in X.\n        \\]</div>\n        Unlike weak convergence on \\(X^*\\) (which requires convergence when tested against all functionals in \\(X^{**}\\)), weak-star convergence only requires convergence when tested against the canonical images of elements of \\(X\\).</p>"
