      "answerHtml": "<p>The closed unit ball of the dual space \\(X^*\\) of any normed space \\(X\\), defined as \\(\\overline{B}_{X^*} = \\{ L \\in X^* : \\|L\\|_{X^*} \\le 1 \\}\\), is compact in the weak-star topology \\(\\sigma(X^*, X)\\).\n        - **Metrizability and Sequential Compactness:** If \\(X\\) is a separable normed space, the weak-star topology on the closed unit ball \\(\\overline{B}_{X^*}\\) (and on any bounded subset of \\(X^*\\)) is metrizable. Since compact metric spaces are sequentially compact, it follows that when \\(X\\) is separable, any bounded sequence in \\(X^*\\) contains a weak-star convergent subsequence.</p>"
