      "questionHtml": "Write the definitions of \\(\\rho(T)\\), \\(\\sigma(T)\\), \\(EV(T)\\), \\(\\sigma_p(T)\\).",
      "strategyHtml": "",
      "keyStepsHtml": "<div class=\"formula\">\\[\n           \\rho(T) = \\{ \\lambda \\in \\mathbb{C} : \\lambda I - T \\text{ is bijective and } (\\lambda I - T)^{-1} \\in L(X) \\}.\n           \\]</div><div class=\"formula\">\\[\n             \\sigma_p(T) = \\{ \\lambda \\in \\mathbb{C} : \\lambda I - T \\text{ is not injective} \\} = \\{ \\lambda \\in \\mathbb{C} : \\ker(\\lambda I - T) \\neq \\{0\\} \\}.\n             \\]</div>",
      "answerHtml": "<p>Let \\(T : X \\to X\\) be a bounded linear operator on a Banach space \\(X\\).\n        1. **Resolvent Set \\(\\rho(T)\\):**\n           <div class=\"formula\">\\[\n           \\rho(T) = \\{ \\lambda \\in \\mathbb{C} : \\lambda I - T \\text{ is bijective and } (\\lambda I - T)^{-1} \\in L(X) \\}.\n           \\]</div>\n        2. **Spectrum \\(\\sigma(T)\\):** The complement of the resolvent set, \\(\\sigma(T) = \\mathbb{C} \\setminus \\rho(T)\\). It is partitioned into:\n           - **Point Spectrum \\(\\sigma_p(T)\\) / Eigenvalues \\(EV(T)\\):**\n             <div class=\"formula\">\\[\n             \\sigma_p(T) = \\{ \\lambda \\in \\mathbb{C} : \\lambda I - T \\text{ is not injective} \\} = \\{ \\lambda \\in \\mathbb{C} : \\ker(\\lambda I - T) \\neq \\{0\\} \\}.\n             \\]</div>\n           - **Continuous Spectrum \\(\\sigma_c(T)\\):** \\(\\lambda I - T\\) is injective and has dense but non-surjective range.\n           - **Residual Spectrum \\(\\sigma_r(T)\\):** \\(\\lambda I - T\\) is injective and its range is not dense in \\(X\\).</p>"
